    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of the <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong>, making sure to separate the grains</p><p>Once hot, remove the pan off the heat and add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan back to the heat and sprinkle your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>into the pan</p><p>Pour in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and mix it all together</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the<strong> spinach</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> to the pan (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up, then sit your <strong>smoked basa fillet[s]</strong> over the rice and cook, covered, for an initial 7-8 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 4-5 min, break the <strong>basa</strong> into chunks in the pan with a wooden spoon, stir it through the rice and cook, covered, for 1-2 min further or until the basa is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once cooked, add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and stir it all together until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>smoked basa & spinach pilau rice</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-basa-and-spinach-pilau-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoked basa & spinach pilau rice </strong>with the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>sprinkled over the top</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Season<strong> </strong>generously<strong> </strong>with<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
